description:
In this second, final volume of "Genetic Grunge" (the first volume appeared in 2002), a series of murders among the Crusaders alerts Umma and her friends. Is Siba trying to kill anyone who comes close to the "Abomination," or are the murders the work of a Crusader who whants to eliminate the competition?

An accident reveals the sect responsible for the crimes, forcing them to escape from New York, Umma already on their heels. She knows she will have to handle things carefully if she wants to keep the Penitent safe. What she doesn't know is that Lordy has her own plans for the Penitent and she is ready to use the Blue Vatican to exact her revenge.
name: Time Out

volume.name: Green Arrow Year One Special Sneak Preview

description:
A new direction in the FATHOM Universe continues! Believing the undersea threat from Vana to be over, Aspen Matthews returns to the surface to try to resume a normal life and finds an old flame waiting for her upon her arrival--Chance Calloway. Meanwhile, tensions rise beneath the surface as the true extent of Vana's scheme begins to manifest, and she reveals her actual target--the Capital city of the Blue, Muria! Writer David Wohl, artist Alex Konat and colorist Beth Sotelo team up once again to bring you the latest adventures of Michael Turner's most beloved creation!

description: The crisis in Hollow Earth comes to a cataclysmic end. Back on the surface, the Majestic 12 invasion of Tesladyne Island is a complete success. Hey, at least things can't get any worse. Right? Wrong. Get ready for the most mind blowing and world changing installment of Atomic Robo ever.

description: Dinah reaches the end of her long battle... but what lies in wait for her to find? Even with the full might of the mausoleum behind her, can she truly raise a hand against her friends and former allies? And what final sacrifices must be made to restore peace to the tormented town of Bizenghast?
name: Vol. 8

description: The World Unfolds as Wilshire and Dirt learn more about life among Prophet's underground gladiators, and Wilshire is caught in a conflict between ordinary citizens and the draconian cops of the Outcaste bazaar. Wilshire must defy Prophet's orders to save the lives of innocent bystanders, but the consequences will be more dire than he could ever imagine!

Sela makes the switch from teacher to student in this issue and hears the fairy tale of swords. Throughout the tales of legend magic swords have always played a part. But what ties does Sela's own sword have to the swords of legend? Find out in this issue.

description:
The geeks shall inherit the earth in this New York Times best-selling series!

This is the fifth volume of an ongoing manga series that is sure to appeal to today’s manga fans in the same way The Big Bang Theory appeals to geeks.

Recent high school transfer student Hasegawa Kodaka is pathetically inept at making friends. Kodaka is an outcast, with his natural blond hair which he inherited from his deceased English mother, and his unpleasant, fierce gaze. When he comes across the brash loner Mikazuki Yozora, who typically chats with her imaginary friend, the two outsiders become the unlikeliest of allies.

Realizing that they have no hope of a normal social life, the two rejects decide to form a group called “The Neighbor’s Club” in order to make friends and maybe even learn a thing or two about social skills. As luck would have it, five new members join the club who are more socially awkward than they are. Will these quirky misfits ever make normal friends, or are they all doomed to social failure?

  • Side Story 1: Binding Magic Release!
  • Club Activity Log 22: A Day at the Pool
  • Side Story 2: The Manifestation of the Demon Astaroth!!
  • Club Activity Log 23: A Visit to the Kashiwazaki Residence (Part 1)
  • Club Activity Log 24: A Visit to the Kashiwazaki Residence (Part 2)

description: David recounts the events that led to his dismissal from the Mercenary while traveling with Eric on a renegade mission involving Synergy's newest space shuttle, the Ark. Meanwhile, Leo is brought to Synergy's Northeast Tower to face interrogation for his crimes.
name: Chapter Two

description: When the world's smartest and most dangerous man goes rogue, there's only one person who can handle the situation: his damaged and broken predecessor. Meet Spencer Cradle, the second smartest man on the planet. Cradle's objective: hunt down the genetically-altered super-intelligent menace known as John Knowledge. On the battlefields of the 21st Century, it's no longer important to be the strongest or most athletic soldier. You have to be the smartest.
name: Part Two: The Revolution Will Not Be Televised

description: As Raymond West, the only surviving member of the family responsible for the global stasis, flees discovery, we learn more about the strange power the Wests possess and how they've influenced America throughout its history. Famous authors fill the pages as the search for Raymond rages in this tale for all the ages.

Molly and Austin have to take down the Sultan of Super Speed, Slipscott before he gets away with a sack of cash. Meanwhile, Commander Holder growing discomfort creates a wedge between herself and Molly.

Unlike his fellow Masters of Spinjitzu, Zane is not human. In fact, technically he's very similar to the Nindroids-the ninjas' newest enemies! So what will happen when Zane, feeling alone and apart from his teammates, is invited to join the Nindroids? Will Zane betray his friends? Also featuring an all-new Green Ninja story!

Note: The digital edition (1/22/2014) for this issue was released before the print edition (2/5/2014).
name: Night of the Nindroids

description:
The Outdoorsman heads south of the border, for tacos, tequila and monster hunting! Joining friend and fellow hunter Ignacio "Nacho" Guerrero in a small Mexican town, the two encounter the worst infestation of chupacabra either have ever witnessed. With no one left alive in the town, it's these two expert monster hunters against a horde of blood-sucking beasties!

The Outdoorsman: Tacos Al Cabron is the second in a series of digital comics from artist Patrick Hoover.
name: Tacos Al Cabron -or- The Secret Ingredient

description:
Sabrina Manga: The Magic Within Vol. 4 collects Sabrina the Teenage Witch #90-100.

The popular manga-style take on Sabrina the Teenage Witch returns with a fourth fantastic installment! Full of romance and the paranormal, Sabrina is torn between two worlds and two boys while attending both a mortal and magical high school. When Sabrina is granted a magic wand, will she be able to control the magnitude of magic it possesses, or will it control her? Throw in a hidden pirate ship, unicorns, elves and the battle of a lifetime, and you're in for a whirlwind of supernatural suspense! It's Sabrina as you've never seen her before in an enchanted adventure brought to you by super-talented writer/artist Tania Del Rio, collecting her acclaimed run on everyone's favorite teenage witch!
name: Volume 4

volume.name: Sabrina the Teenage Witch: The Magic Within

description:
Shadow and Team Dark versus an invading alien army! "Shadow Fall" Part Two: The mission to save humanity is falling to pieces! With Rouge, Omega and G.U.N. on the run from murderous aliens and Shadow battling for his life -- and his free will -- against the malicious Black Death and Eclipse, the world is running out of time! Loyalties are tested, aliens are blasted, and NEW characters make their debut in this space-faring new issue! Featuring cover art from Tracy Yardley!

Note: The digital edition (1/22/2014) for this issue was released before the print edition (2/5/2014).
name: Shadow Fall Part Two: A Shadow In the Dark

description:
All Hell breaks loose as Trish and her friends are dangerously confronted by those under the surface, and the group must tragically separate for their own good. However, a bigger surprise waits for Trish, as she discovers secrets about herself that will forever change her life-for better...or worse! Aspen's own Vince Hernandez is joined by the artistic talents of Giuseppe Cafaro and Andrea Dotta to bring to you Aspen's newest hit series, TRISH OUT OF WATER!

description:
Can a super-villain really go straight? Would they even want to?

Former super-villains and now married couple working penny-ante jobs, Simon and Nancy keep it on the downlow. The only real links to their infamous past is dressing up for each other.

But when a former high-up villain shows them how to be criminals, not villains, can they really resist the urge to slip back into the masks?

WAR OF THE ROSES

New deadly witches keep entering the scene, and everyone -- even the S-class witch hunter Vihyungrang -- has their hands full struggling to survive one magical battle after another. Meanwhile, an extremely powerful witch named Rose appears, and none of the A-class hunters can vanquish her. Can Tasha, Halloween, and their motley crew of allies and rivals stop arguing long enough to take her down?
